spans.text: While the hushed breeze its last weak whisper blows , And lulls old HUMBER to his deep repose
the long lustre of her silver line

forth vindictive through a venal land : In vain Corruption sheds her golden dews , In vain Oppression lifts her iron hand ; He scorns them both , and , armed with truth alone , Bids Lust and Folly tremble on the throne
meets mine car with warbles wildly free , As swells the Lark's meridian ecstasy
Fond Youth ! to MARVELL'S patriot fame
To arts like these devote thy tuneful toil , " And meet its fair reward in D'ARCY'S smile
